(1) Install Packages Locally In The Project (Syntax)
-----------------------------------------------------
==> npm install Package_Name

EX: (Installing Sass) [Here Sass Installed As Production Dependency]
---------------------
==> npm install node-sass [Or] npm install node-sass --save
==> After Install Note That A Folder Called [node_modules] Is Created And Contains [node-sass] Package Folder


EX: (Installing Sass) [Here Sass Installed Locally As Development Dependency]
---------------------
==> npm install node-sass --save-dev


(2) Different Between dependencies And devDependencies
---------------------------------------------------
==> "dependencies": Packages required by your application in production.
==> "devDependencies": Packages that are only needed for local development and testing.

